HEADWORD: Britzska
<hw>Britz"ska</hw> <pr>(br⟦icr⟧ts"k⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Russ. <ets>britshka</ets>; cf. Pol. <ets>bryczka</ets>, dim. of
<ets>bryka</ets> freight wagon.]</ety> <def>A long carriage, with a
calash top, so constructed as to give space for reclining at night, when
used on a journey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

